  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Local Cooperation Fund (LCF) in Bosnia-Herzegovina</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Locally-focused, interactive, independent media is underdeveloped in Bosnia and Herzegovina. While the international community has helped launch initiatives to encourage government transparency, there is still more work to be done in regard to building capacity in media organizations that will monitor BiH&#xE2;&#x80;&#x99;s integration process. Independent media like VESTA Radio plays a vital role in the development of the civil society and the promotion of democracy. VESTA&#xE2;&#x80;&#x99;s Community Media and Citizen Journalism Project aims to strengthen local media and encourage engagement with listeners. VESTA Radio is BiH&#xE2;&#x80;&#x99;s only non-profit, independent, community radio station. Unlike other Western nations, BiH does not yet have a fully developed, independent public radio system.</narrative>
  </description>
